title: Perfect simulation of real pinball
comment: The physics engine is uncanny. The ball once managed to perfectly balance on a top rail on the default table. Of course, with no tilt function, I had to restart a game that I was doing well on.  The game also perfectly simulates the awkward situation of sometimes not launching the ball hard enough at the start. I don't know how these developers do it.  Also, I notice that with the recent updates, the game now also perfectly simulates those old decrepit pinball games I used to play at the convenience stores, you know, the ones with the paddles that would get stuck in the up position, forcing me to mash the buttons to get them back down. I swear, I don't know how these developers do it!

title: the best!
comment: Way back in 1994 I had an EpicMegagames' DOS pinball game called Android. Now I have a phone that runs on Android (no relation, obvz)... and Vector Pinball is astonishingly good. I didn't think I would ever find another virtual pinball game as good as the old Epic Android, but this is it. I like simplicity and the bare-bones graphics are perfect. I have the music off but the sound effects are PERFECT and so nice just in themselves. It's taking me a while to get used to playing with a touch-screen and I've accidentally hit the Home key a few times - gotta keep my hands further up the screen, obviously :) I love this game to bits. Thank you dev!
